com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.document.data

Class DynamicDocumentDataAsMapAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.foreach.across.modules.dynamicforms.domain.document.data.DynamicDocumentDataAsMapAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<String,Object>
    Deprecated. 
    prefer using an EntityPropertiesBinder

    public class DynamicDocumentDataAsMapAdapter
extends Object
implements Map<String,Object>
    Adapter exposing a DynamicDocumentData instance as a flattened Map. Useful when requiring a type that can be used with a DataBinder.

    Note single value methods like get(Object) and put(String, Object) should not be any slower than using the DynamicDocumentData directly, but others like keySet(), containsKey(Object), containsValue(Object) and size() can be very slow as they will first retrieve the entire flattened list of fields.

    When retrieving keys or values, only the distinctly registered fields will be returned. It can be possible to set a different property path using put(String, Object), but not have that path present in the key collection; for example for indexed fields.

    You can configure this adapter for databinding by setting a binderPrefix, and optionally specifying a ConversionService that should be used for input type conversion.

    Since:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:

      • setBinderPrefix

        public void setBinderPrefix(String binderPrefix)
        Deprecated. 
        Prefix when the map is being used for data binding. If set and an exception occurs when setting a field value, it will be rethrown as a ConversionNotSupportedException with PropertyChangeEvent information.

        The binder prefix would usually be the name of a property for this adapter instance on the object being bound. For example: 

        
 public class MyObject {
     public DynamicDocumentDataAsMapAdapter getDataMap() {}
 }
        If a DataBinder is used for MyObject, then the correct binderPrefix to set would be dataMap.

      • setConversionService

        public void setConversionService(org.springframework.core.convert.ConversionService conversionService)
        Deprecated. 
        Optionally set a ConversionService that should be used to convert the input value to the required field type. It no ConversionService is set, the actual value must match the expected field type or a ClassCastException will occur.

        If a ConversionService is set, type conversion will be attempted and exceptions will only be thrown if conversion failes.
